index c81cb24dfa..f4189bbcbb 100644
--- a/docs/api/session.md
+++ b/docs/api/session.md
@@ -1416,7 +1416,16 @@ for `frame` context types.

 Registers preload script that will be executed in its associated context type in this session. For
 `frame` contexts, this will run prior to any preload defined in the web preferences of a
-WebContents.
+WebContents. When `scope` is omitted, Electron preserves the existing frame
+preload behavior: scripts run in the main frame, and also in subframes when
+`nodeIntegrationInSubFrames` enables subframe preloads. Use `scope` to make
+frame injection explicit: `main`, `sub-frames` or `all`. This controls script
+injection only and does not enable Node.js integration in page scripts.
+
+For `dedicated-worker` and `shared-worker` contexts, scripts run as plain
+JavaScript in the worker global scope before the worker's main script is
+evaluated. Dedicated workers have Node.js globals only when
+`nodeIntegrationInWorker` is enabled.

 Returns `string` - The ID of the registered preload script.

